<div id="review_548651797" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/548651797" />
    <a title="Geri Reads" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11757728-geri-reads"><img alt="Geri Reads" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1487874758p2/11757728.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/548651797?book_show_action=true">Feb 28, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Geri Reads" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Geri Reads" href="/user/show/11757728-geri-reads">Geri Reads</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer548651797" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18250058986057901120">I loved this one when I first read it, oh, about 18 years ago...give or take. Unfortunately, I&apos;m not too crazy about it now. I still liked it but the constant misunderstanding, Victoria&apos;s wishy-washiness, Jason&apos;s cruelty grated on me. For example, Victoria&apos;s penchant for putting herself in danger would have been fine with me years ago, but now, oh my gawd! I can&apos;t even. And Jason Fielding felt unnecessarily cruel to me.<br/><br/>Still, I enjoyed this one. The writing did feel dated but it&apos;s Judith McNaugh</span>
  <span id="freeText18250058986057901120" style="display:none">I loved this one when I first read it, oh, about 18 years ago...give or take. Unfortunately, I'm not too crazy about it now. I still liked it but the constant misunderstanding, Victoria's wishy-washiness, Jason's cruelty grated on me. For example, Victoria's penchant for putting herself in danger would have been fine with me years ago, but now, oh my gawd! I can't even. And Jason Fielding felt unnecessarily cruel to me.<br /><br />Still, I enjoyed this one. The writing did feel dated but it's Judith McNaught. Reading this again gave me a sense of nostalgia of the good old days where heroines were special snowflake Mary Sues and rapey heroes roam romancelandia. If I had read this one now, I definitely would've hated it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18250058986057901120" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


