<div id="review_830406779" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/830406779" />
    <a title="Raine" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27288811-raine"><img alt="Raine" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1416553295p2/27288811.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/830406779?book_show_action=true">Jan 21, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Raine" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Raine" href="/user/show/27288811-raine">Raine</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780743467100" href="/book/show/1958990.Once_and_Always">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27288811-raine?shelf=tame-historical-romance">tame-historical-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27288811-raine?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27288811-raine?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27288811-raine?shelf=regency">regency</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27288811-raine?shelf=abuse">abuse</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27288811-raine?shelf=0-read-2016">0-read-2016</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27288811-raine?shelf=pages-0400-to-0499">pages-0400-to-0499</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27288811-raine?shelf=zz_2016-dhasg-yearly-challenge">zz_2016-dhasg-yearly-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27288811-raine?shelf=0-read-2017">0-read-2017</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27288811-raine?shelf=virgin">virgin</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer830406779" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16007035594351600091">Found this paperback treasure under my bed and decided to read it since it was a slow day at work and I&apos;m working from home today. I haven&apos;t read it years, but I still love it! I had given it a 5 star rating when I first put it on my GR account and I wouldn&apos;t change it for the world. <br/><br/>I am now for the most part reading romance erotica, but I still love to go back and re-read these wonderful books. Some of these older books with little or no explicit sex are still such a treasure. For these author</span>
  <span id="freeText16007035594351600091" style="display:none">Found this paperback treasure under my bed and decided to read it since it was a slow day at work and I'm working from home today. I haven't read it years, but I still love it! I had given it a 5 star rating when I first put it on my GR account and I wouldn't change it for the world. <br /><br />I am now for the most part reading romance erotica, but I still love to go back and re-read these wonderful books. Some of these older books with little or no explicit sex are still such a treasure. For these authors who write without all the sex that have people flocking to buy books nowadays really have to ensure that the plots and characters are strong and engaging. And as with most of her books Ms. McNaught definitely hits them out of the ballpark. I felt for the heroine, Victoria, and absolutely detested the hero, Jason. <br /><br />The thing about this story is that, yes, Jason did rape Victoria the first time they had sex. Unfortunately a lot of the 80s romances did feature this theme though the language wasn't as explicit, which I think was why it was able to be 'glossed' over. Of course now, the new readers of these books are finding this very distasteful, though I think the mindset of the romance genre back during the 80s found this somewhat acceptable hence the old term 'bodice rippers'. Of course I don't find this acceptable. No means no, but I think as this is purely fictional like most films out today I have to take the story as it was intended - just a story.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16007035594351600091" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


